<p><span>In compliance with the <span>Clery</span> Act of 1990, BYU-Idaho&nbsp; provides information to students, employees, and prospective students and employees concerning campus crime statistics and campus security policies and procedures.&nbsp; BYU-Idaho&nbsp;strives <span>to provide</span> a safe academic environment for its students, staff, faculty and patrons.&nbsp; The university complies with the <span>Clery</span> Act and o<span>ther</span> federal reporting disclosures and releases <span>an&nbsp;</span></span><a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/security/campus security report.pdf">annual safety report</a><span>(PDF)<span>&nbsp;each</span> year.&nbsp;The report also provides information for accessing university and community resources for crime prevention or assistance if you become the victim of a crime.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span>To request a <span>paper&nbsp;copy</span> of the annual safety report, or for inquires regarding <span>Clery</span> Act issues, please contact the following individual:</span></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><a href="http://web.byui.edu/Directory/Employee/gundersong"><span>Garth <span>Gunderson</span></span></a><br />University Security Director</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span>150 <span>Kimball</span></span><br />525 S. Center Street<br /><span><span>Rexburg</span>,ID 83440</span></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">(208) 496-3000</p>
<p><strong>Biennial Drug and Alcohol Report:</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>Questions regarding BYU-Idaho's policy regarding drugs and alcohol may be found in the University's Biennial <a href="http://www.byui.edu/dean-of-students/biennial-drug-and-alcohol-report">Drug and Alcohol Report</a>.&nbsp; For more information please contact the following individual:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Wynn Hill</p>
